1. Introduction
---------------

Websh is a rapid development environment for building powerful and
reliable web applications. It is a standard Tcl extension and is
released as Open Source Software. Websh handles everything from HTML
generation to database-driven web applications, JSON REST APIs, and
real-time Server-Sent Events (SSE).

Originally developed by Netcetera AG, Switzerland, and contributed
to the Apache Software Foundation in 2001.

Find more information about

- Apache:                      http://www.apache.org/
- Netcetera AG, Switzerland:   http://netcetera.ch/
- Tcl:                         http://tcl.tk/

Key features:
- CGI and Apache module (mod_websh) deployment
- Request routing (web::dispatch)
- URL generation (web::cmdurl)
- Form data and multipart/form-data parsing
- Session management (file-based)
- JWT encode/decode
- Server-Sent Events (web::sseStart, web::sseSend)
- Logging (web::log, web::loglevel, web::logdest)
- URL encoding/decoding, HTML conversion
- Cryptographic utilities and random bytes


